- Context: This is the second page of the COSHH assessment guide PDF.
- Text: 4. Definitions
Hazard
A substance or activity that could cause harm.
Risk
The likelihood of harm arising from a hazard.
Hazardous
Substances
Substances that can cause harm to people’s health. These can be chemicals,
products containing chemicals, fumes, dusts, vapours, mists, gases, and
biological agents.
COSHH
Control of Substances Hazardous to Health.
Safety Data
Sheets (SDS)
A document providing information on hazardous substances including safe use and
potential health effects.
Exposure Limit
Workplace Exposure Limits (WELs) are occupational exposure limits that are set to
help protect the health of workers. WEL is the concentration of hazardous
substances in the air, averaged over a specified period, referred to as a time-
weighted average (TWA). Two time periods are used:
•
Long Term Exposure Limit (LTEL) - 8 hours
•
Short Term Exposure Limit (STEL) - 15 minutes
5. COSHH Assessment Process - Step-by-Step
Step 1: Identify Hazardous Substances
Identify all hazardous substances present in the workplace. This can be achieved by:
•
Reviewing Safety Data Sheets (SDS).
•
Consulting with employees and safety representatives.
•
Checking product labels and container markings.
•
Conducting a thorough workplace walk-through.
